7. Libitinam. Venus Libitina was the old Italian goddess of death, identified afterwards with Proserpine. Attached to her temple was a store of biers and other requisites for funerals. Hence Libitina some- times means ‘burial' and some edd. so take it here, to avoid a tautology with non omnis mon'ar. Most readers will prefer the tautology.
